<p><b>Fossils</b> (from Classical Latin <i>fossilis</i>, literally "obtained by digging") are the preserved remains or <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trace_fossil">traces</a> of animals (also known as zoolites), plants, and other organisms from the remote past. The totality of fossils, both discovered and undiscovered, and their placement in <i>fossiliferous</i> (fossil-containing) <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rock_(geology)">rock</a> formations and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sedimentary_rock">sedimentary</a> layers (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stratum">strata</a>) is known as the fossil record.

